import React from "react"; import { useParams } from "react-router-dom"; import "../scss/pages/ProductDetails.scss"; import { useEffect } from "react"; // import "../assets/js/price"; function ProductDetails() { const { womenProductItems } = useParams(); useEffect(() => { // Wrap your code in this useEffect to ensure it runs after the DOM is ready const priceRange = document.getElementById("price-range"); const rangeValueMin = document.getElementById("range-value-min"); const rangeValueMax = document.getElementById("range-value-max"); if (priceRange && rangeValueMin && rangeValueMax) { // Add the event listener only if the elements exist priceRange.addEventListener("input", updateRangeValues); function updateRangeValues() { const [min, max] = priceRange.value.split(","); rangeValueMin.textContent = min; rangeValueMax.textContent = max; } } // Clean up the event listener when the component unmounts return () => { if (priceRange) { priceRange.removeEventListener("input", updateRangeValues); } }; }, []); // The empty dependency array ensures this runs only once after the initial render return (
